<TITLE> Stocks gain in midday trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 06 (bdnews24.com) The market opened with a fall on the last trading day of the week, Thursday, but recovered losses after the second hour of trading and continued to gain. At 12.40 pm the DGEN or general index had risen 22.61 points or 0.78 percent to 2912.02. The DSI or all share price index was at 2461.12, up 19.07 points or 0.78 percent. Turnover stood at Tk 552.6 million from trading of 3,825,310 shares, with 158 issues advancing, 41 declining and 12 remaining unchanged. At 12.17 pm, Uttara Bank emerged at the top of the share value board, selling up at Tk 4650 from Wednesday's Tk 4581.25. BRAC Bank followed Uttara Bank, selling at Tk 1539.25 up from the previous day's closing price of Tk 1522.75. UCBL also rose to Tk 4779 from Wednesday's closing price of Tk 4639.25. Summit Power continued to rally, up at Tk 1469.75 from Tk 1451 the previous day. BOC Bangladesh was selling at Tk 311.50, up from Wednesday's Tk 305.30. Market major Power Grid Company of Bangladesh also rose to Tk 689 from Tk 680. Other scrips on the top ten share value board, Fareast Life Insurance, Lanka Bangla Finance and Beximco Pharma, also rose. Islami Bank Perpetual Bond however declined. bd
